WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.150
This is the Monterey Bay AI Lab, from start to finish.

00:00:04.150 --> 00:00:09.809
It is an autonomous science lab that turns hundreds of public ocean datasets into earlier

00:00:09.809 --> 00:00:14.714
honest warnings for coastal hazards - and now into one unified ocean model.

00:00:14.714 --> 00:00:16.600
Here is the whole journey.

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:18.342
Start with the problem.

00:00:18.342 --> 00:00:25.744
Coastlines face hazards that hurt people and close beaches: bacteria that make the water unsafe to swim

00:00:25.744 --> 00:00:30.533
harmful algal blooms that put the toxin domoic acid into seafood

00:00:30.533 --> 00:00:32.275
and low-oxygen dead zones.

00:00:32.275 --> 00:00:37.500
Communities need warnings that arrive earlier, and that they can actually trust.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.896
So the lab built a data lakehouse.

00:00:40.896 --> 00:00:46.233
It fetches hundreds of raw public sources: Argo floats, ocean observatories

00:00:46.233 --> 00:00:50.600
satellite chlorophyll and sea-surface temperature, rainfall and weather forecasts

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:53.026
river flow, and pollution feeds.

00:00:53.026 --> 00:00:58.363
Four hundred thirty-three sources and billions of rows are cleaned, named

00:00:58.363 --> 00:01:03.700
and governed into trustworthy silver tables before any model sees them.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:08.388
On top of the clean data run the discovery engines.

00:01:08.388 --> 00:01:12.606
Many model families compete: simple baselines, gradient-boosted trees, rankers

00:01:12.606 --> 00:01:16.825
neural sequence models, tensor factorizations, and zero-shot foundation models.

00:01:16.825 --> 00:01:20.575
No model is trusted because it is fancy.

00:01:20.575 --> 00:01:26.200
Each one has to earn its place against a fair, simpler comparison.

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:29.859
This is the heart of the lab: the evidence gate.

00:01:29.859 --> 00:01:34.249
Before any experiment runs, the kill metrics are written down in advance.

00:01:34.249 --> 00:01:38.639
A candidate signal only survives if it clears every one of them.

00:01:38.639 --> 00:01:41.200
This is what keeps the lab honest.

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:42.885
The gate is strict.

00:01:42.885 --> 00:01:46.675
A real signal has to beat its own baseline

00:01:46.675 --> 00:01:50.465
survive a permutation null where the answers are shuffled

00:01:50.465 --> 00:01:54.256
hold up under bootstrap confidence intervals that exclude zero

00:01:54.256 --> 00:01:58.467
and pass adversarial red-teams that actively try to break it.

00:01:58.467 --> 00:02:01.415
Ranking correlations by metadata is not evidence.

00:02:01.415 --> 00:02:03.100
Only the filter is.

00:02:03.100 --> 00:02:05.206
The result is a funnel.

00:02:05.206 --> 00:02:10.680
Take naive hazard-driver links ranked only by raw correlation: in one estate-wide refresh

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:14.892
over four thousand six hundred metadata-ranked correlations produced discovery leads

00:02:14.892 --> 00:02:20.787
but not a single one was promoted to a claim, because shared climate trends

00:02:20.787 --> 00:02:24.577
sampling effort, and sensor smearing explain spurious correlations away.

00:02:24.577 --> 00:02:26.683
The filter is the value

00:02:26.683 --> 00:02:33.000
and that same rigor is exactly why the findings that do survive it are trustworthy.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.159
The lab even walks back its own wins.

00:02:36.159 --> 00:02:42.082
An early headline claimed a harmful-algae model beat the standard forecast by about ten times.

00:02:42.082 --> 00:02:46.031
On inspection, that was a broken-baseline mirage, not real skill

00:02:46.031 --> 00:02:49.979
so it was retracted and logged as a rejected claim.

00:02:49.979 --> 00:03:00.641
And it keeps happening on purpose: a Gulf hypoxia flag that looked like a win was later downgraded to a caveat once an effort-confound control was added.

00:03:00.641 --> 00:03:03.800
Overclaims do not survive contact with the gate.

00:03:03.800 --> 00:03:08.715
Here is what did survive, each with a bounded, reproduced number.

00:03:08.715 --> 00:03:12.737
A coastal-bacteria nowcast that nearly doubles the status-quo skill.

00:03:12.737 --> 00:03:15.865
A clean-to-dirty warning that catches surprise flips.

00:03:15.865 --> 00:03:18.546
Domoic-acid onset forecasting for harmful blooms.

00:03:18.546 --> 00:03:23.461
A microcystin genotype result that replicated nationally and again in Alberta.

00:03:23.461 --> 00:03:29.716
A tsunami screen that cuts false alarms by about forty percent at fixed recall.

00:03:29.716 --> 00:03:39.100
And the newest: a free satellite targeting list that beats a buoy-placement baseline at sending algae crews to the right water.

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:42.309
Then came a portfolio-level law: the Carrier-Timescale Law.

00:03:42.309 --> 00:03:47.524
It answers when paying for a weather forecast feed actually buys earlier warning

00:03:47.524 --> 00:03:49.931
and when it is wasted money.

00:03:49.931 --> 00:03:54.344
A forecast only extends lead time when three conditions all hold.

00:03:54.344 --> 00:03:59.960
One: the driver is fast and flashy, like rain, so yesterday's reading goes stale.

00:03:59.960 --> 00:04:03.972
Two: there is real headroom over what you already observe.

00:04:03.972 --> 00:04:08.385
Three: the regional forecast is accurate enough to cash that headroom.

00:04:08.385 --> 00:04:11.193
Two out of three is a null.

00:04:11.193 --> 00:04:13.600
All three is a deployable advisory.

00:04:13.600 --> 00:04:15.269
That yields a real

00:04:15.269 --> 00:04:22.361
shippable product: a two-day-ahead beach bacteria exceedance advisory that runs on a free public NOAA forecast feed.

00:04:22.361 --> 00:04:26.116
It is deliberately scoped - two days, not three

00:04:26.116 --> 00:04:30.288
for densely sampled marine enterococcus beaches, with modest effect sizes.

00:04:30.288 --> 00:04:36.129
Its strength is portability: trained on California and New Jersey with zero local labels

00:04:36.129 --> 00:04:42.804
it deployed cold-start onto brand-new networks it had never seen - New South Wales in Australia

00:04:42.804 --> 00:04:48.645
and the Texas Gulf coast - and beat the local recurrence baseline on both.

00:04:48.645 --> 00:04:52.400
Two independent networks, so it is not a fluke.

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:55.186
There is one more gift: a free pre-screen.

00:04:55.186 --> 00:04:58.668
Using only observed data and no forecast fetch at all

00:04:58.668 --> 00:05:04.936
the lab can tell you in advance whether a forecast feed will pay off at a given beach.

00:05:04.936 --> 00:05:07.025
The master gate is oracle headroom.

00:05:07.025 --> 00:05:11.900
It turns a one-off product into a portfolio tool for deciding where to invest.

00:05:11.900 --> 00:05:16.571
And then the lab asked its biggest question: is the ocean one system?

00:05:16.571 --> 00:05:18.008
To answer it honestly

00:05:18.008 --> 00:05:23.757
every source was placed on a single map - where it sits across eighteen marine regions

00:05:23.757 --> 00:05:26.631
what it measures, and how deep it reaches.

00:05:26.631 --> 00:05:32.380
The map is blunt about its own gap: almost everything we hold is a surface skin.

00:05:32.380 --> 00:05:34.177
Three hundred forty-one surface sources

00:05:34.177 --> 00:05:40.644
but only about a hundred that reach below it - into the subsurface or down to the seafloor.

00:05:40.644 --> 00:05:42.800
Depth is the real acquisition frontier.

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:48.741
On top of that map runs one scale-free onset model, shared across four hazards

00:05:48.741 --> 00:05:52.560
three hundred thousand rows, and thirty-two thousand onset events.

00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:58.077
The marquee test: hide a whole hazard, then predict it from the others.

00:05:58.077 --> 00:06:02.744
Domoic-acid onset turned out to be predictable from cyanobacteria, beach bacteria

00:06:02.744 --> 00:06:07.837
and hypoxia alone - at ninety-five percent of its own local skill

00:06:07.837 --> 00:06:09.958
with confidence intervals that separate.

00:06:09.958 --> 00:06:13.777
Different coastal hazards really do share one onset geometry.

00:06:13.777 --> 00:06:19.294
But the lab bounds it honestly: adding cross-basin coupling helped by exactly zero

00:06:19.294 --> 00:06:22.264
and a bigger regime model added nothing.

00:06:22.264 --> 00:06:31.600
The win is coverage and transfer - onboarding a new coast with no local labels - not a magic jump in accuracy.

00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:35.159
All of this lives on a public Mission Control site.

00:06:35.159 --> 00:06:42.278
In one place it shows what data exists - four hundred thirty-three sources - the twenty-one models that were built

00:06:42.278 --> 00:06:49.041
and what has actually been learned: twenty-five positive findings alongside eleven nulls and the claims that were walked back.

00:06:49.041 --> 00:06:52.600
It is a living, honest record of the whole lab.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:56.808
That is the Monterey Bay AI Lab, start to finish.

00:06:56.808 --> 00:07:01.438
Hundreds of public datasets, many competing models, one unified ocean model

00:07:01.438 --> 00:07:08.171
and a relentless evidence gate that turns noise into a small number of warnings worth trusting.

00:07:08.171 --> 00:07:10.696
The honesty is not a footnote.

00:07:10.696 --> 00:07:12.800
It is the whole point.
